[
  "Jonathan Nelson is CEO of Providence Equity Partners, the private equity firm he founded in 1989.",
  "Providence has invested in more than 160 companies, many in the media, communications, education and information industries.",
  "The firm sold scuba-diving certification company PADI in 2017 for over $700 million, three times its initial investment.",
  "In 2019, Providence sold its majority stake in automotive software firm OEConnection for nearly $1.3 billion, tripling the investment it made in 2016.",
  "Nelson serves as a trustee of Rockefeller University and on the board of the Institute for Advanced Study."
]